Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.25,0:00:06.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn you...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.37,0:00:12.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Marito!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.67,0:00:19.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All units, spread out!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.30,0:00:23.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No go, huh? I thought that if it was\Nalso using lightning to attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.55,0:00:26.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,there would be an opening\Nwhile it switched over.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.55,0:00:29.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Looks like it isn't going\Nto be that easy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.77,0:00:32.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In which case, what are\Nour other options...?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.52,0:00:34.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Marito!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.98,0:00:38.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Message from the Deucalion!\NHQ has ordered us to pull out.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.98,0:00:40.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Pull out? All our forces?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.86,0:00:44.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dales and Orlov Platoons should\Nhave gotten the order by now.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.99,0:00:45.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.82,0:00:46.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But what?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.66,0:00:50.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Retreat! Retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.16,0:00:53.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dales 22!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.60,0:00:54.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where is he?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.71,0:00:56.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the enemy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.84,0:00:58.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.38,0:01:02.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That invisible Kataphraktos we failed\Nto destroy is over there.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.63,0:01:03.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Crap.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.80,0:01:07.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Clydesdale Leader to Orlov\NLeader, can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.72,0:01:09.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Retreat!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.14,0:01:11.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is... Orlov Leader{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.60,0:01:13.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Impossible...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.52,0:01:18.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the... only...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.44,0:01:28.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lightning and Invisibility...\NAnd one other?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.37,0:01:32.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Order them to continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.58,0:01:35.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Encircle and eliminate.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.21,0:01:37.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As you wish, Milord.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.13,0:01:47.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Asseylum?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.26,0:01:49.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.72,0:01:51.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have done all I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.56,0:01:56.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The rest is up to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.81,0:02:03.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Slaine...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.12,0:02:10.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.48,0:04:04.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dales 11!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.03,0:04:12.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Clydesdale Leader!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.74,0:04:15.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kaizuka Jr.!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.04,0:04:27.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please pull out! The smoke screen should\Nobstruct the enemy's vision a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.96,0:04:29.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Go!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.26,0:04:30.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,R-Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.39,0:04:37.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Plus... We can use this\Nsmoke to attack.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.89,0:04:42.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Found him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.69,0:04:44.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To the right! Get clear!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.90,0:04:54.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mustang Leader!\NWhat's going on, Kaizuka,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.41,0:04:56.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were going\Nto keep Lightning busy!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.83,0:04:57.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sorry.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.83,0:05:01.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Its fire suddenly shifted, like it was\Nconcentrating in your direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.54,0:05:03.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Crap...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.25,0:05:09.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're surrounded?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.09,0:05:11.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.52,0:05:24.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Deucalion?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.53,0:05:32.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damage report!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.36,0:05:34.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're okay! We're managing\Nto discharge it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.86,0:05:37.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Set us down and extract\Nall Kataphraktoi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.28,0:05:40.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here, ma'am? That's right in\Nthe middle of the enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.12,0:05:41.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're landing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.08,0:05:44.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,KCAS, 10 knots.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.91,0:05:46.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're descending too fast,\Nand there's a strong tail wind!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.88,0:05:49.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're okay! The Aldnoah drive\Nis handling it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.50,0:05:53.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Antigrav device to maximum!\NVertical speed, 1,200 feet per second!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.34,0:05:58.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Get aboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.55,0:06:01.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Guide in Dales Platoon, hurry!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.60,0:06:05.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Open ventral hatch!\NRetrieve all Kataphraktoi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.81,0:06:10.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At our 9 o'clock!\NEnemy Kataphraktos closing in!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.57,0:06:13.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fire main guns!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.49,0:06:20.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kataphraktoi retrieval complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.91,0:06:22.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We're leaving!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.29,0:06:27.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.79,0:06:31.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Another enemy Kataphraktos to aft!\NSame type as the one we just destroyed!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.88,0:06:32.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Reinforcements?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.80,0:06:36.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Another at our 2 o'clock! These\Naren't reinforcements! They're...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.36,0:06:56.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Enemy returns, 12... 16... 24...\NNumber keeps climbing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.82,0:06:58.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A duplication ability?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.36,0:06:59.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All ahead full!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.78,0:07:00.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.13,0:07:16.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Weather radar, Doppler radar,\Nboth offline!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.30,0:07:20.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Crap... Our discharge system must've\Nbeen damaged by Invisibility's arrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.26,0:07:21.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Radio's out, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.72,0:07:25.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,GPS display lost,\N2D radar also offline!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.27,0:07:26.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.47,0:07:28.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stay calm! Continue ascent!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.64,0:07:30.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.94,0:07:37.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see. You are amenable to serving\NCount Troyard, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.32,0:07:38.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.32,0:07:40.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall pass word along at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.82,0:07:43.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There is one other favor\NI would ask of you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.28,0:07:44.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.58,0:07:47.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Might I be granted an audience\Nwith Princess Asseylum?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.70,0:07:50.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What? A personal audience\Nwith Her Highness?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.25,0:07:53.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yes. And if possible,\Nwith Count Troyard as well.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.63,0:08:00.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is no small task... However, I will\Nendeavor to see that you are accommodated.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.13,0:08:03.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It will come at a price.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.60,0:08:05.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I understand.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.18,0:08:10.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I must say, defeat normally causes\Na man to lose his way, but not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.10,0:08:11.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Beg pardon?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.06,0:08:12.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Getting into the good graces\Nof not only Count Troyard,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.98,0:08:16.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but Princess Asseylum as well,\Nwould be most beneficial.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.86,0:08:20.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However, do not wear your\Nambition on your sleeve.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.15,0:08:23.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is a chance that\Nit might trip you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.37,0:08:24.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Of course...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.87,0:08:33.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Princess Asseylum is an imposter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.09,0:08:38.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going into space.\NPrepare a shuttle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.63,0:08:42.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations on your victory,\NMilord Slaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.93,0:08:46.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is no cause for celebration,\Nnot when the enemy escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.22,0:08:50.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The objective of securing territory\Nwas accomplished.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.39,0:08:52.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is that not success enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.73,0:08:56.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is sure to cause more knights\Nto swear loyalty to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.27,0:09:03.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We cannot let our guard down. Nothing is less\Nreliable than a knight's vow of loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.66,0:09:05.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am well aware, Milord.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.78,0:09:11.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And about that request from Count Barouhcruz?\NWhat answer shall I give?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.08,0:09:12.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.26,0:09:13.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milord?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.33,0:09:18.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Mazuurek, his name was? If he wants to\Nsee the princess, let him see her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.67,0:09:23.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She is happily fulfilling her role\Nof extending our power base.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.63,0:09:26.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For the time being, at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.52,0:09:38.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use. This goes\Nway beyond a quick fix.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.94,0:09:44.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're kidding... Night vision's also out,\N so I can't even fly by eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.41,0:09:48.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's malfunctioning?\NThe sensor system?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.78,0:09:51.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How did you know, Lt. Kaizuka?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.79,0:09:56.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's easy to tell. It's faint, but\Nthe fuselage is carrying a charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.62,0:10:00.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With this ship, engine-related malfunctions\Nare unlikely. In which case...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.80,0:10:04.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A-Anyway, help us out!\NWe're all kinds of screwed!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.10,0:10:16.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should lower our altitude a little.\NLow enough to keep us off enemy radar.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.69,0:10:21.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But the altimeter and GPWS are both dead,\Nso I'm scared to take us too low.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.86,0:10:24.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell how high we are.\NWe're at 9,200 now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.24,0:10:27.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can see all that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.82,0:10:30.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can you also pick up\NVOR stations?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.99,0:10:32.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.08,0:10:36.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once you have both signals,\Ntell me. I'll calculate our radial.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.62,0:10:37.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.25,0:10:40.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What's our heading?\NI was trying to put us on 110.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.92,0:10:42.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're almost there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.50,0:10:45.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fly at an offset of 3 degrees for 2 minutes.\NThen straighten out and maintain heading.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.43,0:10:51.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad... Are we caught\Nin some nasty turbulence?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.35,0:10:54.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like it goes on for a while.\NJust to be safe, you should...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.18,0:10:55.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've got this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.44,0:10:59.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can handle this much.\NSame goes for earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.19,0:11:04.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I see. From here on out, it looks like\Nit's experience that's most important.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.61,0:11:06.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Once I pick up an LLG,\NI'll let you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.82,0:11:07.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.16,0:11:11.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.78,0:11:14.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, we should be\Nthanking you for earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.45,0:11:18.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Marito was pretty surprised that\Nyou would do something so crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.29,0:11:23.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"You're the last person I want to hear\Nthat from." Tell him I said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.30,0:11:26.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.13,0:11:30.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Preparations for the founding\Nare proceeding smoothly, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.84,0:11:31.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.64,0:11:35.56,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can hardly wait for\Nthis new kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.56,0:11:37.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And to be able to go\Nto your homeworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.73,0:11:40.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is a world inhabited\Nby vulgar trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.60,0:11:43.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is hardly the restful place\Nconjured up by the word "home."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.73,0:11:48.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rather, I never had such\Na place to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.40,0:11:51.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Neither did I.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.74,0:11:56.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is nowhere that\NI might find solace,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.20,0:11:58.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,neither on Vers\Nor in royal standing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.42,0:12:04.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Slaine. Anywhere that I may\Nbe together with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.13,0:12:07.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,more than anywhere else,\Nthat is my...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.80,0:12:13.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You honor me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.93,0:12:18.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall call on you\Nagain later, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.22,0:12:21.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Slaine, dinner is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.19,0:12:28.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies, but there are still pressing\Nmatters that I must attend to.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.82,0:12:30.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.75,0:12:46.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ina-
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.05,0:12:54.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Inko.\NWhat's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.43,0:13:00.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Um, about yesterday. Nina was gushing\Nabout how you helped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.35,0:13:02.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.56,0:13:05.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.81,0:13:06.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What would be wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.94,0:13:08.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.15,0:13:12.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Look, it's nothing, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.36,0:13:16.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think about the enemy\Ncoordinating their actions?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.83,0:13:21.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they're so hard pressed that they've\Nbeen forced to swallow their pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.41,0:13:25.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Judging from the outcome, I don't\Nthink we have much to fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.63,0:13:30.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you suppose it's connected\Nto that proclamation, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.05,0:13:34.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That Orbital Knight named Slaine Troyard\Nwho is behind Princess Asseylum...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.26,0:13:37.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The way I hear it,\Nhe one-ups even Kaizuka Jr.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.35,0:13:42.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If this opponent really is setting things\Ninto motion with a goal in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.18,0:13:47.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,it's not a simple scheme that we can\Ncounter with just superior resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.48,0:13:48.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Enter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.07,0:13:53.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,PFC Matsuribi, entering.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.24,0:13:57.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Message from HQ, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.66,0:14:01.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A request for reinforcements?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.91,0:14:06.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Launch all-out attack on\Ncaptured territory and retake it."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.04,0:14:08.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Throw sheer numbers at them?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.63,0:14:14.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's the long and short of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.72,0:14:18.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And how have you\Nbeen feeling since?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.60,0:14:21.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Physically, I feel fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.85,0:14:27.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My memory, however...\NIt is still rather hazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.31,0:14:33.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is hardly surprising. The very fact that\Nyou regained consciousness was a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.44,0:14:35.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.74,0:14:41.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please do not force\Nyourself to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.99,0:14:43.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Slaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.87,0:14:49.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid that I must take my\Nleave now. Please get some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.75,0:14:50.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.67,0:14:52.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall return.\NPlease look after Her Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.09,0:14:56.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, Milord Slaine...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.93,0:15:03.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can guess what it is\Nthat you wish to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.64,0:15:08.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The proclamation, yes? Taking me as her\Nhusband and founding a country...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.73,0:15:13.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That proclamation issued\Nby Princess Lemrina
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.65,0:15:17.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,was entirely the result of\Nthe weakness in my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.45,0:15:20.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Princess Asseylum\Nis sure to wake up."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.16,0:15:27.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to hold on to that belief but failed,\Nhaving given up somewhere deep down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.79,0:15:36.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But then a miracle happened, as if to\Nreprimand me for being such a fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.92,0:15:39.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,With the situation having\Nchanged so drastically,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.26,0:15:43.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,what I must think about now is,\Nhow can I make Her Highness happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.01,0:15:45.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That, and that alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.77,0:15:51.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But what of Princess Lemrina?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.44,0:15:55.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As to what she is looking for...\NI can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.90,0:16:01.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The same thing as me, I suspect.\NA place where she can find solace.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.70,0:16:07.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But that is something that\Nneither of us will ever obtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.66,0:16:10.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We mustn't tell her everything yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.83,0:16:16.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But even if she looks down on or derides\Nme for what I am doing here,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.05,0:16:19.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I do not particularly mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.34,0:16:24.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's ironic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.01,0:16:28.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I had waited with such hope\Nfor Her Highness to awaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.06,0:16:34.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But now, what I hope for is that\Nher memory never returns.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.61,0:16:39.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your newfound resolve to serve\Nmy trusted Count Troyard
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.44,0:16:43.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,fills me with such joy\Nthat I cannot contain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.70,0:16:46.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your Highness is too kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.41,0:16:49.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am fully prepared to serve\Nboth Your Highness
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.12,0:16:52.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and Count Troyard with\Nwholehearted devotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.71,0:16:55.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I, too, was touched by\NCount Mazuurek's drive
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.75,0:17:02.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,as he swore to rise up once again\Nfor the sake of Vers' future
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.13,0:17:04.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,even as he was held\Nprisoner on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.39,0:17:06.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Begging Your Highness' pardon...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.35,0:17:11.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am given to understand that you once\Nunderwent similar hardships on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.27,0:17:15.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, something similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.61,0:17:19.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Terrans are all such... vulgar trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.19,0:17:24.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There was not a single one that\NYour Highness grew close to?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.91,0:17:27.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Close to? I think not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.41,0:17:31.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I left all interaction with Terrans\Nto my handmaiden.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.96,0:17:38.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I once entertained the notion of\Nreconciling with those people,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.13,0:17:41.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but I now see what a fool I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.34,0:17:48.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why is Slaine not here\Nat a time like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.01,0:17:52.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Slaine is rushing about, making\Npreparations for the new operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.85,0:17:55.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He said as much earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.06,0:17:58.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He has been locking himself away in\Nhis castle far too often lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.90,0:18:01.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever he is doing,\Ncan he not do it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.15,0:18:04.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am told that precious\Nresources are involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.65,0:18:07.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then I shall go to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.20,0:18:08.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Highness, you-
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.66,0:18:11.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall go over\Nto the Landing Castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.79,0:18:13.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your Highness!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.42,0:18:19.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you unharmed, Highness?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.46,0:18:20.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I do apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.55,0:18:22.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How long will it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.01,0:18:30.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, how long will it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.06,0:18:37.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I shall see you\Nto your room, Highness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.46,0:19:05.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please pardon the delay, Count Mazuurek.\NPlease follow me to the parlor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.30,0:19:08.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to have finished\Nchecking my credentials.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.26,0:19:09.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I deeply apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.80,0:19:13.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all, it is I who\Ncommitted a grave blunder.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.01,0:19:16.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To think that my\Nship broke down...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.14,0:19:18.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How fortunate for me that\Nyou were in the vicinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.82,0:19:25.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see... Count Troyard\Nis still at the moonbase.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.94,0:19:28.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Milord. I regret to say\Nthat you have missed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.53,0:19:32.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Lord Harklight is on\Nhis way here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.99,0:19:36.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I made my move as soon as I was\Ncertain that he was not here.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.87,0:19:42.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Troyard is commuting between here and\Nthe moonbase more than is necessary.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.00,0:19:46.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meaning that the princess'\Nlocation must be...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.97,0:19:58.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.69,0:20:01.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are these Terran flowers?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.31,0:20:03.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.61,0:20:07.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This castle has undergone\Nquite the transformation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.61,0:20:09.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can tell, Milord?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.57,0:20:12.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was an acquaintance\Nof its former master.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.16,0:20:16.49,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He detested all things Terran, fearing\Nthat they harbored microorganisms.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.37,0:20:21.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no such worry here.\NTerran flowers are perfectly safe-
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.21,0:20:23.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you have been to Earth, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.79,0:20:27.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, that is only\Nwhat I have heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.17,0:20:32.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I had heard that Princess Asseylum had\Nan attendant, but I did not expect-
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.14,0:20:37.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No. I mean... Her Highness\Nwent to Earth alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.85,0:20:40.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No one is speaking of Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.94,0:20:45.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I-I must be going!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.57,0:20:51.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You truly have not gone there? Do you\Nknow what happened on Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.24,0:20:55.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What about a boy named\NInaho Kaizuka?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.50,0:21:04.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How long will it be...\NTell me, sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.50,0:21:12.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How long will it be before you release\Nyour grip on his feelings?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.58,0:21:14.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,For me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.01,0:21:19.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Milady. He said that he\Nwanted me to give it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.48,0:21:23.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To the princess who\Nknew about Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.20,0:21:42.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.05,0:21:55.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Milady!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.76,0:21:59.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.15,0:22:07.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I...
